llama_3_models.notes: Llama models are open source and free to use. The cost comes from hosting and inference on cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure) or via third-party API providers (Together AI, Replicate). There is no official 'pro' tier from Meta.

pricing_analysis.subscription_adoption_rate: High - Consumer subscriptions are becoming the primary access method for individuals, priced competitively around $20/month.
pricing_analysis.trend: Aggressive price competition and a push towards massive context windows. New entrants like DeepSeek and Qwen are setting extremely low per-token prices, forcing established players to release more efficient, lower-cost models (GPT-4o, Gemini Flash) and bundle services into attractive subscriptions.
